.TH LCSD 8 "2026-05-11" "lcsd 1.0.4" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
lcsd \- Lightweight Cluster Service daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lcsd
.B \-c
.I CONFIG
.RB [ \-\-daemonize ]
.RB [ \-\-no\-syslog ]
.RB [ \-\-no\-timestamp ]
.RB [ \-v | \-vv | \-vvv | \-vvvv | \-\-verbose ]
.br
.B lcsd
.B \-\-version
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lcsd
is a small Linux high-availability daemon that manages virtual IP addresses
(VIPs) across a cluster. VIP ownership is protected by short-lived majority
leases. A node may activate a VIP only after quorum grants the lease, and it
must renew that lease continuously to keep the VIP active.
.PP
All configured nodes are voting members for quorum and lease decisions.
Nodes with role
.B full-member
may run VIP resources. Nodes with role
.B quorum-only
vote and participate in leases but never manipulate VIP addresses.
.PP
Peer communication uses persistent TCP connections. Idle liveness is maintained
with lightweight heartbeat frames. Full cluster state is exchanged when peers
join and when ownership or resource state changes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-c " CONFIG" "\fR, \fB\-\-config " CONFIG
Read configuration from
.IR CONFIG .
The default path is
.IR /etc/lcs/lcs.conf .
.TP
.B \-\-daemonize
Fork into the background. Foreground mode is the default and is recommended
when running under systemd.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-syslog
Disable syslog output. This is useful under systemd because journald already
captures foreground stderr.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-timestamp
Disable timestamps in foreground stderr output. This is useful under systemd
because journald adds its own timestamps.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Increase log verbosity. The flag may be repeated as
.BR \-vv ,
.BR \-vvv ,
or
.BR \-vvvv .
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the daemon version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print usage information and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file uses an INI-style format. The same cluster definition
should be present on all nodes; only the local
.B node
key in the
.B [cluster]
section changes per host.
.SS Cluster Section
.TP
.B name
Cluster name. Must match on all nodes.
.TP
.B node
Local node name. Must match one configured
.B [node NAME]
section.
.TP
.B bind
Local address for daemon-to-daemon TCP. If omitted, the daemon binds all
addresses.
.TP
.B port
Default peer TCP port. The default is 3322. Individual nodes may override it.
.TP
.B socket
Local Unix control socket path for
.BR lcs (8).
The default is
.IR /run/lcs/lcsd.sock .
.TP
.B lease_ms
Lease lifetime in milliseconds. The default is 5000.
.TP
.B renew_ms
Lease renewal interval in milliseconds. The default is 1000.
.TP
.B peer_timeout_ms
Peer liveness timeout in milliseconds. The default is 5000.
.TP
.B secret
Optional shared cluster secret checked during peer handshake.
.TP
.B syslog
Whether syslog logging is enabled by default. The default is true.
.TP
.B vip_backend
VIP address-management backend:
.B ip
or
.BR netlink .
.TP
.B metrics
Enable the Prometheus metrics endpoint. The default is true.
.TP
.B metrics_bind
Metrics bind address. The default is 127.0.0.1.
.TP
.B metrics_port
Metrics TCP port. The default is 9120.
.SS Node Sections
Each
.B [node NAME]
section defines a voting cluster node.
.TP
.B role
Either
.B full-member
or
.BR quorum-only .
.TP
.B address
Peer address, either IPv4, IPv6, or a hostname.
.TP
.B port
Optional per-node peer TCP port override.
.SS Group Sections
.B [group NAME]
sections define placement rules for VIPs.
.TP
.B type
Either
.B keep-together
or
.BR anti-affinity .
.TP
.B mode
Either
.B strict
or
.BR best-effort .
.SS VIP Sections
Each
.B [vip NAME]
section defines one managed VIP resource.
.TP
.B address
VIP address in CIDR notation.
.TP
.B interface
Linux interface on which the VIP is configured.
.TP
.B group
Optional placement group name.
.TP
.B priority
Positive integer priority inside the group. Higher numbers are higher priority.
If omitted, priority is derived so earlier sorted VIPs have higher priority.
.TP
.B home_node
Optional preferred full-member node for this VIP. When the node is online, LCS
places and rebalances the VIP there unless automatic return has been blocked by
a manual move away from home. A later manual move back to the configured home
node clears that block.
.TP
.BR pre_start ", " post_start ", " pre_stop ", " post_stop
Optional absolute paths to hook programs executed around VIP activation and
removal. Hooks receive environment variables such as
.BR LCS_CLUSTER ,
.BR LCS_NODE ,
.BR LCS_VIP ,
.BR LCS_ADDRESS ,
.BR LCS_INTERFACE ,
.BR LCS_EVENT ,
.BR LCS_EPOCH ,
and
.BR LCS_LEASE_ID .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/lcs/lcs.conf
Default daemon configuration.
.TP
.I /run/lcs/lcsd.sock
Default local control socket.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/system/lcsd.service
Packaged systemd unit on many distributions.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGTERM
Gracefully shut down. Locally owned VIPs are released before exit.
.TP
.B SIGINT
Same as SIGTERM, typically used when running in the foreground.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lcs (8),
.BR ip (8)
